Then she'll go for long leash walks, excited to see other dogs and pulling on her harness. Back home, she'll want her playtime - and her frozen peanut butter Kong. Then at night she'll want to snuggle and cuddle in bed with her people. With her cute light snore, she makes a perfect sleep partner. Sugar is also a smart girl who understands 'sit,' 'no' and 'stay,' and she's perfectly house-trained. She isn't a fan of crates, but does fine free-roaming the house when her fosters are away. This sweet, lovable girl hopes to move in with a family. She'd love children and another dog to play with who would give her constant affection - and snacks. Come meet her, she loves everyone right away and will follow you home!

animal.description:
Hi! I'm Buzz! I was adopted from Dogwood as a puppy, but things changed and I was passed around for a while before being abandoned altogether. Animal Control finally came and rescued me, though. I'm doing much better now, but I am always going to be a little bit special. When confronted with specific, or strange unpredicted sounds, I don't know how to respond. I get overwhelmed easily- and when I do, I cope by either self-harm by chasing and chewing on my tail or by trying to control the situation that has left me overstimulated. My behaviors are pretty well in line with a compulsive disorder- something that never will be able to be cured. A vet indicated that if my anxiousness gets worse, it may be a good idea to start me on medicine to help gain some control. But I promise I'm one of the sweetest guys you will ever meet! I love to cuddle and play. My favorite game is tug-of-war. And playing games and with toys actually helps me feel better! 

I need a mature home. Children would be too unpredictable and noisy for me to relax. I would also do best in a home with other dogs that are as playful as I am- though they need to be tolerant of me socially because I can get my signals crossed sometimes. I'm good with cats. Like going to the dog park. House trained. Crate trained- I just need plenty of time for exercise with an appropriate amount of stimulation. So tell me, what's not to love! If you have any questions, please don't be afraid to ask. While I might have some special needs, I promise I'm a good boy! Primary Color: Brown Secondary Color: White Weight: 30.6lbs Age: 2yrs 3mths 1wks Animal has been Neutered

animal.description:
Name: Ziggy
Nickname: Zigster, Big Z, Pumpkin
What we know he is: Chihuahua
What he thinks he is: 100 lb. German Shepherd
Age: 3 Years
Weight: 9 lbs. 
Before OMD: Found on the streets as an emaciated stray by animal control and did his mandatory hold at the shelter. We saw him, he reminded us of one of our favorite OMD alums, Zig, and we knew he had to be part of our crew.
Energy Level: High. He can handle a long hike and still come home and enjoy some play time.
Affection Level: Higher. Cuddles, snuggles, more cuddles, more snuggles, add in some kisses…you get the picture.
Food Motivation Level: Highest. He didn’t pack on those much needed pounds magically! This boy can eat!  
Vocal Level: Surprisingly low.
Best Feature: His “OMG! You’re back!” tail wag and happy dance that happens every time he sees a human -- even if he just saw them.
Claim to Fame: Lightening fast tail-chaser (his own) extraordinaire.
His favorite things: All things soft and fluffy (only families with incredible blanky collections need apply). Laying on his back. Shimmying down the couch through said soft things. Throwing his toys around. 
Our favorite things: He is a lover for sure. He wants love and to be loved. His humans are his happiness. He makes a fantastic work-from-home partner.
Working on: Not guarding things he buries in his dog bed. Occasional marking. Jumping. Talking trash to passing dogs.
Dogs: Eh. Maaaaaybe not...unless his family is very savvy with intros. He has lived with dogs in his foster homes but was kiiiiiiind of a jerk for the first few weeks and does not like to share his people. 
Cats: Yeah, no problem. May chase from time to time just for fun.
Kiddos: Hard pass. He is not a fan of young ones. To be clear: we will be looking for homes with no children or homes with kids 12+.
Crate Trained: Sure is! He sleeps in his crate every night.
Housebroken: Mostly, but still falls back into his occasional marking behaviors. Hey, old habits die hard.
Home Requirements: Standalone, apartment, condo -- any environment will work as long as he's allowed on the furniture for cuddle time!
Ziggy is neutered, vaccinated, heartworm negative, and microchipped. He is available for adoption to residents of CT and surrounding states. If you are interested in adopting, please complete an application at omdrescue.org

animal.description:
Meet Kiwi! She is a 3 year old French Bulldog / Pitbull Terrier mix, around 50 lbs, spayed, up to date all vaccines and is ready for her furever family. Her name is Kiwi because when she came into rescue (from a high kill shelter), most of her fur was gone and when it started growing back, it looked like kiwi fuzz! 

See, Kiwi is silly most of the time, and is interested in being a couch potato (she would love it if you were too)! She is learning to play fetch and likes to play tug a war in small increments. Kiwi asked me to tell y’all ‘food & cuddles is life’. If you’re interested in a pretty princess, she is always down for a manicure.

She loves her humans but is sometimes fickle about other fur friends as she loves to be the center of attention. This is why she would likely be happiest in a home with no other pets. And even if you don’t want to cuddle, Kiwi demands it. Kiwi is looking to be someone’s new best friend who she can trust to love her the right way. She is heartworm positive but has begun treatment and is doing great! Apply to adopt Kiwi and get ready for all the cuddles! 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2020 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

animal.description:
Sweet Annabella is a mostly furry, extremely loveable couch potato. She has been with her foster mom for the past 6 months recovering from Demodectic mange and getting more beautiful every day. She has been a perfectly polite and trainable dog. She is very food motivated which makes training a breeze. Annabella knows commands like sit, shake, and down. She also gets along great with the cat in the home and a 60 lb male dog, although Annabella will do best as either an only dog or with a submissive male. She has a rough and silly play style and will not do well with small dogs. While she would get along with another submissive male dog in the home it would not be necessary as she loves the companionship of a human above all else. She does great with kids who are a little older, she does not typically jump on anyone but sometimes she doesn't realize how big she is, and in all honesty if she could sit on your lap all day she would. She is not the most athletic dog, but walks great on leash. Annabella is not an adventurous dog and prefers short neighborhood walks as going to new places can be very over-whelming for her. Her short burst of energy and excitement are short lived and she settles down great. She meets new humans in a polite and sweet manner but has not had much experience meeting new dogs. She gets a bath with medicated shampoo about once a week as her skin continues to heal. Annabella is housebroken and crate trained. Annabella would prefer a quite neighborhood over city life.

If you are interested in adopting Annabella, please fill out an application today!

animal.description:
Jamie is handsome, he responds well to commands, has a precision touch to getting squeakers out of toys. He does well with other dogs with a proper introduction. Jamie needs a confident leader when walking on a leash. When you feel confident Jamie feels confident. Jamie takes his cues from his owner! Jamie needs a secure yard, he is able to leap fences in a single bound (he aspires to be the next superman). Jamie is potty trained. He is not good with cats. He is neutered, in good health, and up to date on all his vaccinations. He is approximately 8 years old and 80 pounds and would most likely be more comfortable at 70 to 75 pounds. He loves to go on walks, ride in the car and cuddle with his humans and most importantly be by your side. The perfect home would be someone that walks everyday (even a good run), that is home more than not and will dote on this lovely boy. Jaime is looking for a human who loves dogs and enjoys cuddling him on the couch and the bed. He would do best in a house with a secure fence with humans that are willing to give him the love, attention, and stability he needs. Jaime has done well with other dogs but needs a proper introduction. He loves life - especially dog toys, loving pets, car rides, playing, smelling new things, and receiving gentle pets. He wants to be in a home where he receives positive reinforcement and regular attention. He wants to please and likes to communicate with his humans. He is very loyal and will make you feel safe and protected. He is currently working with trainer and dog behaviorist Karyn Garvin (
https://garvinsdivinedogtraining.com/).

*Applications to adopt: wwwTucsonColdWetNoses.com Home Visit / ID and Residence Verification is required. Compliance does not imply or guarantee adoption. Approval is the sole discretion of CWN representative(s).

animal.description: Kapu is 12 years old, but shh don't tell him that - he has no idea that he's a "senior. Kapu was originally adopted from us and then recently came back into our care during the COVID-19 pandemic. Kapu came to us with an old injury that was causing him pain. Thanks to our Second Chance Fund, we were able to get Kapu the help he needed to live his best life. He is a gentle, fun-loving soul who adores hanging with humans, and enjoys the company of other dogs. He loves his stuffed toy ''babies'' and will contently curl up with them for a good nap. He thinks car rides are great and if you're extra lucky, he'll nuzzle up and rest his big ole head on your shoulder while you're driving! Kapu has been spending his days with a wonderful foster family who have been teaching him about the finer things in life and now he's ready for a forever family of his own! Kapu loves romping around, playing with toys, and curling up in bed. He's such a love and we simply adore him. Kapu absolutely deserves to know that forever kind of love.

**Adoption Sponsored!

**ADOPTION SPONSORED BY COLDWELL BANKER BROWN REALTORS!**

Meet Pepper! She originally was given the name Marsha when first arriving to P4P in 2014. Pepper was adopted and loved, but due to unfortunate circumstances, she has found her way back to us. Now 7 years old, Pepper's ready for a new home! A forever home. One that will love her for all that she is! She's still got a zest for life and a love for attention. She is doing very well in her foster home with other dogs, but please no cats for this lady. Pepper loves going for walks, and does so great on a leash. She keeps a very clean kennel. Are you interested in adopting Pepper? Fill out an application today! Her adoption fee is $185, and she is spayed, microchipped and current on all vaccines. Pepper is on a special diet, so her future home will need to understand her food allergies. She in on a strict no-chicken, H/A prescription diet, and it really helps her skin. She gets a bath with medical shampoo twice a week, and will most likely need medication to help with flare-ups every once in a while. The love Pepper has and is waiting to give her forever family is worth it.

Adoption applications are available online at www.partnersforpetsil.org/applications!

animal.description:
Meet Midget 3.5#, 6yr old Chihuahua mix who is sweet, timid, and cuddly. She loves to be with her mom, Toughy, and loves to snuggle deep into blankets. Sometimes you have to look hard to find her. She is rather quiet and prefers to be held as you go about living life. 

Due to her size, medical needs, and the fragility, Midget and her mom are looking for a quiet, adult-only with lots of love and little activity. They should be the only pets in their new home as other dogs would be too much. They have never seen a cat. They would love if their person was always home. 

Midget says "Hi, we would like us to have an adult only home, no other dogs please as we are very quiet and reserved. With my petite size and quiet personality, peace is very important, but so is exercise. We would enjoy a tranquil secure yard to go for little walk-abouts in, but make sure no nasty birds can snatch me. You have to watch over us carefully. Perhaps if you have a quiet home we could have adoption staff set up an interview."

If you have further questions, emails are the only method of communication at this time. We all care about the health of our 2-legged caregivers and the community at large, so as a precaution we are temporarily suspending our public open hours. We are still taking email inquiries and applications, and will be in touch with you as soon as we are able. We appreciate everyone’s understanding during this difficult time! Stay Well!
.
CONTACT INFORMATION:
Email: adoptapetadoptions@gmail.com
Telephone: (360) 432-3091 Leave Message on OPTION 1
Application: https://form.jotform.com/40419164974157
All AAP dogs come up to date on vaccinations, spayed/neutered, and microchipped.

animal.description:
1220060

I am heartworm positive. Heartworm is NOT contagious. The rescue covers the cost of treatment at the rescue's vet. 

I seem to be part pittie, so I need a single family home. I can NOT go to a home in a city or county with pitbull restrictions. 

Reese is a 4 year old lab mix with we think springer spaniel too. She was picked up by the shelter when someone called in a el chupacabra. She is gaining weight and hair slowly. We use coconut oil everyday and oatmeal shampoo for baths. She is shy when you approach her with the leash but we are working on that, sit and down. She loves to play with our dogs and would probably do well with a doggy friend. She loves to sit next to us and be petted. Reese is fine with my older kids (9 and up) and has been gentle with the babies (2 & 1). She just tends to avoid them because they make her nervous. She hasn't been outside a lot because its too cold so we aren't sure about walks. She sleeps in her crate at night but she likes when someone sleeps in the room with her. She loves ropes, tennis balls and stuffies but doesn't understand fetch. Overall a sweetie who is going to be so pretty and fun once she get better/comfortable.

If you are interested in meeting a dog or cat, we require an adoption application. If the animal has "HAS APPLICATION" listed, they are still available to receive additional applications but also may be in the process of being adopted soon. Apply for a DOG: http://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/adoptable-dogs.html

Interested in saving more lives? Foster a dog today! Learn more, see our list of dogs needing foster, and apply, https://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/foster-a-city-dog.html

City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is a foster-based rescue in Washington, DC. We do not have a shelter. We focus on local adoptions in DC and the metro area of Maryland and Virginia. CDR&CK has a thorough adoption process in order to find the best possible fit for each of our dogs and cats (we do not operate under a first-come, first served model).

Upon accepting a new cat or dog into the organization, we provide a basic vet visit that includes necessary vaccinations, disease screenings, deworming, microchips, and spay/neuter (unless specified). We do not provide a comprehensive medical exam prior to adoption. As a result, sickness, injury, and disability may exist unbeknownst to CDR&CK. City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is not responsible for payment of any vet care, including known and unknown medical conditions once a cat or dog is adopted from us. 
Dog specific: Rabies, DHPP, Bordatella vaccines. They are tested for HW, Lyme, Ehrlichia, Anaplasmosis.

Most cats and dogs will have a house training accident in the initial days in their new home and we cannot guarantee any pet is housebroken or crate trained.

We also update our Facebook page daily with new cats and dogs.

animal.description:
Personality: Sensitive, Shy & Playful
Age: 9 Years Old
Size: 29 lbs

Talk about a distinguished gentleman with quite the mysterious side. Barley is the man of your dreams with his large, dreamy eyes, soft coat and polite manners. Did we mention that he's quite the athlete as well? Only if it involves a ball or squeeky toy. He is the full package and then some. It may take some time to truly see his personality flourish, but he'd prefer it that way. His loves takes time and trust is extremely important to him. He's a loyal guy who wants to give his heart to someone who feels the same. Barley would do best in a home without younger children and without other dogs in the home. While he does well with other appropriate dogs after a proper, slow introduction outside the home he would do best in a single dog home. Barley is a highly sensitive guy who needs a home that understands and recognizes fearful behaviors in dogs and will act accordingly as he may act/respond out of fear. 

Barley is neutured, microchipped and current on vaccines. 

His adoption fee is $110. 

If you're ready to take a chance on love please email adoptions@hstt.org or call (530) 587-5948 for more information on how you can schedule an appointment to meet Barley!

Toughy says "Hello, dears. I would like us to have an adult only home, no other dogs please as we are very quiet and reserved. At my age, peace is very important, but so is exercise. We would enjoy a tranquil secure yard to go for little walk-abouts in, but make sure no nasty birds can snatch Midget. You have to watch over us carefully. Perhaps if you have a quiet home that could provide me with steady exercise and my daughter, Midget with security, she is very small, we could have adoption staff set up an interview."

Available 12/20/20. Meet Klondike a 72# 10 month old Texas Blue Lacey. Klondike's breed is the official state dog of Texas. His personality and heart are as big as his home state. This boisterous bundle of energy is looking for active home with sturdy, confident children to love. He is very tidy boy who would prefer to be the king of his castle with no other pets to threaten the throne.

Klondike is big, strong boy who needs a loving, confident family who will give him lots of physical activity and continued training. His potential family should have securely fenced yard with lots of room to run. 

Klondike says "Hello, Washingtonians. It sure does rain a lot here, but I also heard that there are lots of fun places to explore while on leash with my new family. Please understand I don't quite get along with other animals, including fellow canines, at this time due to my sheer size, exuberance, personality, and need for continued positive reinforcement training." 

Please see Breed Information Below:

"Lacys are intelligent, intense, active and alert. Originally created to work feral hogs, the Lacy was developed into an all-around working breed for ranchers, cowboys, hunters and trappers. They have incredible drive and determination. Bold and brave, they excel at herding cattle and hunting wild boar. They are naturally territorial and will protect their property. Though Lacys make excellent companions, they don't do well with passive owners. This breed needs a calm yet assertive leader who establishes clear rules. Lacys also need consistent mental and physical exercise. Due to their intelligence, they can be quickly trained to perform many tasks." https://www.dogbreedinfo.com/bluelacy.htm

animal.description:
Wicket is a 10 year old yorkie, who spent his life being used to sire puppies by a backyard breeder. Despite this, he has bonded with his foster mom and with enough patience to get through his shy period, we're confident he'll bond with a new family quickly. He does fine with other dogs but due to his tiny stature and spinal deformity, we will only place him with dogs of similar size. We do not think he'd do well in a home with children.
When he came to us, he was full of health issues and we've done our best to address them. He had to have all of his remaining teeth pulled due to severe dental disease, he has a spinal deformity that makes him have a hunchback, and he has an oronasal fistula that needs surgically repaired by a specialist. He sees a specialist in January and we will be paying for that surgery; however, he can be adopted in the meantime as long as an adopter is willing to take him to Hilliard for the appointment and comply with his post-op care.
Thankfully, he's an all around happy dog and doesn't seem to let all of his issues dampen his spirits! He is just looking for his retirement home, where he can enjoy the finer things in life for whatever time he has left.
Wicket has been neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, and is heartworm negative. His adoption fee is $250 and he's being fostered in the Columbus area.
If you are interested in adopting Wicket, please apply on our website, www.prodogsohio.org/adoptables.
Photo Credit: Claudine Kosier with Simply Dog Photography
He's being fostered in the Columbus area. Please note, we only schedule meet and greets with approved applicants. We are not currently hosting adoption events due to Covid.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
We appreciate your support, in order to help us continue to rescue dogs! Donations can be made via our PayPal account - info@prodogsohio.org.
You must be willing to commute to the location that the pet is being fostered in order to be eligible to adopt. We do not ship our pets. We also require that you personally bring the pet back to us should the adoption not work out.
We do NOT negotiate adoption fees. All money goes to support our rescue operation. We are 100% volunteered based.
We require your current dog(s) to be current on vaccines and heartworm prevention.
Apply online at www.prodogsohio.org, under the Adoptables tab.
Due to the volume of apps and inquiries, we may not be able to respond to everyone.

animal.description:
Meet Vinny! He is a senior at approximately 10-12 years old and weighs 8 pounds. Somehow he wound up as a stray and was taken to an animal shelter, but nobody came to claim him. He was a favorite among the shelter staff and would stand at the front of his kennel wagging his tail and very happy to meet any visitors. Vinny is great with people as well as small and large dogs. Dogs like Vinny are often overlooked at the shelter but he has so much personality that we knew we could find him a lovely retirement home. We found out that Vinny has some calcification in his spine which causes him to walk stiffly. He will be on medication for that. He also had some seizures which are controlled with medication. We are hoping someone with a big heart will adopt  Vinny and give him a home for his golden years.

If you are interested in meeting Vinny please first fill out the online adoption application at www.greatpets.org. Once your application has been received and reviewed you will be contacted to discuss if he is a good fit for your home. Vinny's $150 adoption donation includes his vet examination, neuter surgery, vaccinations, dental cleaning, flea treatment, and microchip.

Rocky and Levi are friendly, affectionate, and smart. They are eager to please, know their commands, and are potty trained.

animal.description:
Slinky is a 2 year old 14 pound red dachshund - slight mix in that no bend in her front legs and they are a tiny bit longer than a pure doxie. She is a wonderful pal - a bit shy with strangers, but when she warms up she loves her people. Not yet spayed. She is on wait list at our vets. You can meet 'n greet - she just cannot leave until after her surgery.
She is Mom to 7 pups - 4 females; 3 males. Named after Toy Story 4 characters. *All have been adopted. It's just Slinky who's waiting for her home!
Please find our applications and valuable information under 'Adopt a dog'* on our website: *www.beaglesandbuddies.com* and email your application to beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Let us know your preference of appointment day/time and which dogs you are interested in and we will do our best to accommodate and email you the closest appointment available. Please allow us up to a week to get back to you. Most appointments will be Friday-Sunday, 10 am - 2 pm, for an hour.
*Note bring any other dog/s and the entire family to your meet and greet at B&B.* A complimentary training manual is included with each adoption, authored by terristeuben.com. Check out her website - she is fabulous!
B&B is glad to be open during the pandemic. We know the value and comfort of a loving pet companion and are doing our best to help the dogs and folks who need them. We update our website daily and are always rescuing, vetting, rehabilitating, socializing.
* We are accepting applications for volunteers to spend time with our dogs, hang out, sing/read to the shy ones, walk/toss ball with those who go to the playgrounds; cleaning, office work, gardening, and building/repair projects! *

Are you my furrever family?

For further info on the adoption process, please visit our home page and check out the "Adopt a Dog" section, which has thorough instructions. All our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and

fully vaccinated before adoption; they have been wormed, bathed, socialized, walked daily and much loved; each adoptee leaves with a leash, collar, and all medical records.

Our prices are higher than the shelters' because we nurse the dogs through their illnesses and get them needed surgeries and dentals. We also spend time socializing. Furthermore, unlike shelters, rescues do not get financial aid from the government and must rely on donations, grants, and adoption fees. Our fees for adults start at $150 and go up to $750. The higher end is for our most in demand dogs, such as young beagles and other purebred dogs. The lower end is for dogs who have been here a while. For puppies, we may go beyond this and charge $1000. The good news is that, because rescues fall under the "charity" category, the fees for our dogs are officially donations and are therefore tax deductible. You can think of it as donating to a worthy cause and getting a dog in return!

Sponsor Me

Beagles & Buddies must find ways to raise money so we can continue saving dogs. Your tax-deductible donation keeps our rescue kennel operating!

Hours

Friday: 10 am to 3 pm

Saturday: 10 am to 3 pm

Sunday: 10 am to 3 pm

Monday: CLOSED

Tuesday: CLOSED

Wednesday: CLOSED

Thursday: CLOSED



Weekday appointments may be available. We are a small staff and do our best to accommodate your needs. **Note that during COVID, we are not holding open houses on any day. Please email us for an appointment and include your application (found on our website, beaglesandbuddies.com, under "Forms"). Most appointments will be Friday through Sunday, though other days may also be available. We usually schedule one appointment per hour. Allow 1-2 hours for your appointment. Please look at our website and make a list of one or more dogs that you would like to see.

Contacting Us

If you have a question about adopting, giving up a dog, boarding, or volunteering, please visit the appropriate tabs on our
home page.

For more specific questions, call 626-444-9664 (please leave a voicemail if no answer) or email at beaglesandbuddies@gmail.com. Note that
Emailing
is always preferred!

Thanks!

Please note: If you are viewing this profile anywhere other than Beagles & Buddies own website, you are not receiving full info. Visit info on pet here.

animal.description:
Scooby is the perfect size pet!  He is just 27 pounds at 10 months, a very handsome red heeler blend.  He is a bit shy with people he doesn't know, but very gentle and loves to play.  He is here with his brother Shaggy, and the two of them are a dynamic duo!  Both will make wonderful family friends!

To make a meet and greet appointment or for more information, call us at 520-836-0904  We are scheduling all appointments by phone to avoid double booking.  

Effective September 30, our adoption fee is $180 for dogs six months and older ($260 for puppies and $100 for senior dogs) and includes spay/neuter surgery, microchip, rabies, vaccines to date, a free vet check, and a lifetime of love!

Come visit at 15699 W. Aniceto Rd. Casa Grande, AZ 85193.  We are open Wed through Sun, 10 am to 4 pm.

Visit our website: http://www.valleyhumane.net and our Facebook page Valley Humane AZ.
